Asked by @AaronPerryWx how to make a day length map, this is #rstats code for day of year

require(raster)
require(geosphere)
day = 180
r <- raster(extent(-180.05, 180.05, -90, 90), res=0.1)
lat <- lon <- r
xy <- coordinates(r)
dlLats <- daylength(xy[, 2],day)
r[]=dlLats
plot(r) https://t.co/z8hu5h8MpW
